The former Lagos State Deputy Governor, Mrs. Sarah Sosan and renowned Professor Patrick Utomi and others are to lead a symposium on nationwide development on April 24. The hybrid event is slated to hold at JFK Event Hall, Nerdc Road, Alausa Ikeja and also to be streamed online is themed: Accelerating Nationwide Development Via A Bottom-up Approach. It is being organised by Atinuke Odjenima, a leadership and human development consultant passionate about nation-building to mark her 40th birthday. According to her; “this symposium is part of my contributions for the love of country. And it is going to be a yearly meeting intended to amplify the voices of the nation builders’ community and all stakeholders who resiliently continue to intervene and intercede in the actualization of a nation characterized by justice, equity, and fairness.” She continued further; “It presents the opportunity to exchange ideas and present practical steps to value reorientation, and accountability and reinforces belief and hope for a better Nigeria.” Other top guest speakers expected at the occasion are former presidential candidate, Mr Tope Fasua, PhD, a chartered accountant and public policy analyst and Gboyega Isiaka, a former Ogun state governorship candidate. Tito Philips, Jnr. a Lagos based CEO of MADphilips Development Company described Atinuke as a jewel among her pairs adding; “I want to salute her for the various strategic efforts to improve the Nigerian economy and equally wish her more celebrations in good health”.